Meet Paula Gilovich of Denver, Colorado, a social worker focused on helping homeless and at-risk youth feel loved who uses her own deep love for others to inspire service and give her own life meaning and joy.

Jesus claimed he had something no other messenger of truth has: inside knowledge of how things really are. Brian McLaren, author, activist, theologian, and pastor, reflects on the meaning that's at the heart of the incarnation.

Miri Glaser, with Just Vision.org, tells the story of Jamal, a Palestinian Christian in Israel for whom religious identity has become less important than demonstrating to Israel - and the world - that there is a better way to move toward peace and reconciliation.

The founding pastor of Saddleback Church, which began with one family in 1980, Rick Warren is author of the New York Times #1 Best Seller, The Purpose Driven Life. Warren talks about how we'll all be assured justice.

Bison should not be left to the process in nature's provision for the increased human demand for food of bison abundance.

Thomas 'Flo Rida' Gisby joins us in conversation with producers of PeaceJam's The Nobel Conflict Resolution Conference. This program is directed by Jeanene MacLuclan of World Learning.
